    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Xilinx ISE 'Hello World' Tutorial]]></title>
    <link href="http://spyrous.github.io/blog/2014/11/14/xilinx-ise-hello-world-tutorial/"/>
    <updated>2014-11-14T18:52:22+02:00</updated>
    <id>http://spyrous.github.io/blog/2014/11/14/xilinx-ise-hello-world-tutorial</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>In this tutorial I will show a very simple example of creating an <strong>AND</strong> digital gate
with the help of an HDL (Hardware Description Language) <strong>VHDL</strong>. I will run the design on an FPGA board (ZyBo) and then I will also simulate it using ISE 14.7. If you don&rsquo;t have a board it&rsquo;s fine but you can only do the simulation part of this tutorial.<br /><br /></p>

<p>The instruction below is only for the Linux version of ISE. Windows users can skip this and just double-click the icon of ISE and start the tutorial.
After you install ISE run the <strong>source</strong> command on your terminal and then write <strong>ise</strong> to start the application.<br /></p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='bash'><span class='line'><span class="nb">source</span> /opt/Xilinx/&lt;Your ISE version&gt;/ISE_DS/setting64.sh
</span><span class='line'>Example: <span class="nb">source</span> /opt/Xilinx/14.7/ISE_DS/setting64.sh
</span><span class='line'>ise
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p><br /><br /><br />
After a couple of seconds ISE application will be loaded and you are presented with a screen similar to the one below.</p>

<p><img class="center" src="http://spyrous.github.io/images/ISE_Project_1.png"><br /></p>

<p>Click <strong>File</strong> and then <strong>New Project</strong></p>

<p><img class="center" src="http://spyrous.github.io/images/Tooltip_190.png"><br />
Give a <strong>name</strong> to your project</p>

<p><img class="center" src="http://spyrous.github.io/images/New%20Project%20Wizard_189.png"><br />
Here you are asked to fill in the specifications of your board (<em>Family</em>, <em>Device</em>, <em>Package</em>, <em>Speed</em>).
The attributes below <strong>Top-level Source Type</strong> are just a matter of preference.<br />
<em>For example mine is a ZyBo (Zynq Board) so I specify it&rsquo;s attributes accordingly</em></p>

<p><img class="center" src="http://spyrous.github.io/images/New%20Project%20Wizard_191.png"><br /></p>

<p>Last screen is for verification purposes. Check your setup and click <strong>Finish</strong>.</p>

<p><img class="center" src="http://spyrous.github.io/images/New%20Project%20Wizard_192.png"><br /></p>

<p>After that you will be presented with a screen similar to the one below.</p>

<p><img class="center" src="http://spyrous.github.io/images/ISE_Project.png"><br /></p>

<p>To continue right-click the name of your board and then click New Source.</p>

<p><img class="center" src="http://spyrous.github.io/images/Selection_193.png"><br /></p>

<p><img class="center" src="http://spyrous.github.io/images/Tooltip_209.png"><br /></p>

<p>We want to create a VHDL file to program the FPGA so we click VHDL Module
and give a name to it.</p>

<p><img class="center" src="http://spyrous.github.io/images/New%20Source%20Wizard_195.png"><br /></p>

<p>Then we are asked to fill in the ports of the entity we are gonna create.
In this example we will create an two-input AND gate.
So the inputs are a, b and the output is c.<br />
<em>(Don&rsquo;t forget to change the <strong>Direction</strong> column for the output)</em></p>

<p><img class="center" src="http://spyrous.github.io/images/New%20Source%20Wizard_196.png"><br /></p>

<p>Again a verification screen to check that your settings are correct and proceed.</p>

<p><img class="center" src="http://spyrous.github.io/images/New%20Source%20Wizard_197.png"><br /></p>

<p>After you click finish you will be presented with the code similar to the one
below. <br /><em>(NOTE: I removed the comments that are added by Xilinx)</em></p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
<span class='line-number'>8</span>
<span class='line-number'>9</span>
<span class='line-number'>10</span>
<span class='line-number'>11</span>
<span class='line-number'>12</span>
<span class='line-number'>13</span>
<span class='line-number'>14</span>
<span class='line-number'>15</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='VHDL'><span class='line'><span class="k">library</span> <span class="nn">IEEE</span><span class="p">;</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="k">use</span> <span class="nn">IEEE.STD_LOGIC_1164.ALL</span><span class="p">;</span>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="k">entity</span> <span class="nc">test</span> <span class="k">is</span>
</span><span class='line'>    <span class="k">port</span> <span class="p">(</span>
</span><span class='line'>      <span class="n">a</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">b</span>    <span class="o">:</span> <span class="k">in</span>      <span class="kt">STD_LOGIC</span><span class="p">;</span>
</span><span class='line'>      <span class="n">c</span>       <span class="o">:</span> <span class="k">out</span>     <span class="kt">STD_LOGIC</span>
</span><span class='line'>   <span class="p">);</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="k">end</span> <span class="nc">test</span><span class="p">;</span>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="k">architecture</span> <span class="nc">Behavioral</span> <span class="k">of</span> <span class="nc">test</span> <span class="k">is</span>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="k">begin</span>
</span><span class='line'>    <span class="n">c</span> <span class="o">&lt;=</span> <span class="n">a</span> <span class="k">AND</span> <span class="n">b</span><span class="p">;</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="k">end</span> <span class="nc">Behavioral</span><span class="p">;</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<ul>
<li>In the code above I only added the <em>14th</em> line <strong>c &lt;= a and b;</strong><br /></li>
<li><strong>Entity</strong> is the black box that says that we have two inputs ( a, b ) and one output ( c ).<br /></li>
<li><strong>Architecture</strong> says what operations do the inputs and outputs do.<br /></li>
<li><strong>&lt;=</strong> is the assignment operator in VHDL. <strong>AND</strong> is the logical operation that we want to do between the two inputs.</li>
<li>I left a space blank between architecture and begin which is used for further declarations. In this example we will not need any so I leave it blank.<br /></li>
<li>When we say that we have inputs of type <strong>in</strong> it means that we can <strong>ONLY</strong> read values from them. <br /></li>
<li>When we say that we have outputs of type <strong>out</strong> it means that we can <strong>ONLY</strong> write values to them.</li>
<li>VHDL is <strong>NOT</strong> case sensitive so if we say PoRt or port it&rsquo;s the same thing.</li>
</ul>


<p>Here for those who have a board you can continue to Board Implementation.<br />
Those who don&rsquo;t you unfortunately have to skip this part and go to Simulation.<br /></p>

<center><h2> <u>Simulation</u></h2></center>




<center><h2> <u>Board Implementation</u></h2></center>


<p><img class="center" src="http://spyrous.github.io/images/New%20Source%20Wizard_198.png"><br />
<img class="center" src="http://spyrous.github.io/images/New%20Source%20Wizard_199.png"><br /></p>

<p><img class="center" src="http://spyrous.github.io/images/Selection_200.png"><br />
<img class="center" src="http://spyrous.github.io/images/Warning_201.png"><br />
<img class="center" src="http://spyrous.github.io/images/Selection_202.png"><br />
<img class="center" src="http://spyrous.github.io/images/Tooltip_203.png"><br />
<img class="center" src="http://spyrous.github.io/images/Auto%20Assign%20Configuration%20Files%20Query%20Dialog_204.png"><br />
<img class="center" src="http://spyrous.github.io/images/Assign%20New%20Configuration%20File_205.png"><br />
<img class="center" src="http://spyrous.github.io/images/Assign%20New%20Configuration%20File_206.png"><br />
<img class="center" src="http://spyrous.github.io/images/Device%20Programming%20Properties%20-%20Device%201%20Programming%20Properties_207.png"><br />
<img class="center" src="http://spyrous.github.io/images/Selection_208.png"><br /></p>
]]></content>
